Hi, just wanted to let you know that my suggested fix wasn't complete.
There is a third buffer overflow with the same attack vector and impact, that will lead to the same type of crash of the other two. I didn't notice the first time because the length required to make it crash is slightly longer.

The vulnerable code (line 1735 in BabyGrid.cpp):

```c++
    TCHAR tbuffer[255];
    lstrcpy(tbuffer, (TCHAR*)lParam);
```

A possible fix:

```diff
-    lstrcpy(tbuffer, (TCHAR*)lParam);
+    StringCchCopy(tbuffer, 255, (TCHAR*)lParam);
```
